Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cairo - &nbsp;Egyptian President Abdel-Fattah al-Sisi says the government will increase the monthly capacity of ration cards through which it distributes food subsidies from $1.16 per person to $2.77 in an attempt to ease the effects of hard-hitting economic reforms.Al-Sisi said in a speech on Tuesday night that the government has taken several measures to ease economic pressure. These include increasing retirement benefits by 15%, raising wages by 7-10% and expanding the scope of tax exemption eligibility.Egypt floated its currency in November to meet a key demand from the International Monetary Fund, which provided a desperately needed $12bn loan.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.